    <title>xStreamBufferSpacesAvailable</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="stream__buffer_8h" kindref="compound">stream_buffer.h</ref></para>
<para><preformatted>
size_t <ref refid="stream__buffer_8h_1a9a78e0206cb1dc343c329f9db579208d" kindref="member">xStreamBufferSpacesAvailable( StreamBufferHandle_t xStreamBuffer )</ref>;
</preformatted></para>
<para>Queries a stream buffer to see how much free space it contains, which is equal to the amount of data that can be sent to the stream buffer before it is full.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>xStreamBuffer</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The handle of the stream buffer being queried.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>The number of bytes that can be written to the stream buffer before the stream buffer would be full. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
